Personal Habit Improvement System
A clean, interactive React app designed to help you build good habits and break bad ones through consistent tracking and visual feedback.

🎯 Features
Good Habits

Streak tracking - Visual motivation through consecutive day counters
Daily check-offs - Simple, satisfying completion tracking
Category organization - Health, Productivity, and Learning habits

Bad Habits

Days free counter - Track progress breaking unwanted behaviors
Honest tracking - "Slipped up" button to reset without shame
Progress focus - Celebrate improvements, not perfection

General

Custom habits - Add your own habits in any category
Clean interface - Minimal design that doesn't overwhelm
Instant feedback - Real-time updates and visual progress indicators
Built-in tips - Success strategies integrated into the app

🚀 Getting Started
Prerequisites

Node.js (version 16 or higher)
npm or yarn

Installation

Clone the repository
bashgit clone https://github.com/B-Gouthami/Personal-Habit-tracker.git
cd Personal-Habit-tracker

Install dependencies
bashnpm install

Start the development server
bashnpm run dev

Open your browser
Navigate to http://localhost:3000 to see the app

🛠 Tech Stack

React - UI framework
Tailwind CSS - Styling and responsive design
Lucide React - Beautiful icons
Vite - Fast build tool and dev server

📱 Usage

Track Good Habits: Click the circle next to any habit to mark it complete and build your streak
Monitor Bad Habits: Use "+1 Day" when you successfully avoid a bad habit, or "Slipped" if you need to reset
Add Custom Habits: Click "Add New Habit" to create your own personalized goals
View Progress: Check your stats dashboard for motivation and overall progress tracking

🎨 Customization
The app comes with example habits, but you can easily:

Add habits specific to your goals
Remove habits that don't apply to you
Modify categories to match your lifestyle
Adjust the UI colors and styling in the component

🤝 Contributing
Feel free to fork this project and make it your own! Some ideas for improvements:

 Data persistence (localStorage or database)
 Habit scheduling (specific days/times)
 Progress charts and analytics
 Habit sharing with friends
 Mobile app version
 Notification reminders

